title.91: Power Pack & Cloak And Dagger: Shelter From The Storm (1989) #1

description.3: Mojo and the X-Babies decide to crash the scene at a British royal wedding! What they were not expecting was EXCALIBUR being on the guest list!
description.4: Note: this issue does not collect reprinted material from UNCANNY X-MEN (1963) #135. ""Little Boy, Lost!"" A memory from Scott Summer's childhood reveals an intertwined history with Mister Sinister!
description.5: Note: this issue does not collect reprinted material from UNCANNY X-MEN (1963) #136. ""When Dreams Are Dust."" Dr. Robyn Hanover inadvertently exposes a young Scott Summers to a trauma at an air base.
description.6: ACTS OF VENGEANCE The greatest villains of the Marvel Universe band together to take out the heroes! Their first target: Spidey! And the Avenger villain Graviton is the one doing the targeting!
description.7: A group of mysterious robots infiltrate the Hydrobase! With the super-powered Avengers still in the Negative Zone, it's up to Quasar and the non-powered staff to defend their turf.
description.8: While Cap searches for his missing partner on the island of Madripoor, Diamondback fights for her life against the notorious Mr. Phun! Can Cap get to Rachel Leighton before she meets her end? Plus: Crossbones is on the hunt again!
description.16: Conan is hired to steal a magical jewel but things get hairy when Conan is attacked by werecats!
description.17: Conan is alone in the city of werecats!
description.18: The (former) Queen Mother hatches a murderous plot to steal the Power Pack’s powers!
description.19: Will the Power Pack’s stolen abilities be responsible for destroying every last one of the Kymellians?
description.21: Is romance in the future between Captain America and Diamondback? It's a question that neither may live to have answered if Crossbones has his way! Plus: Vagabond becomes the pawn of the Power Broker's heir apparent Dr. Malus!
description.27: Frank's plan to take down a drug-dealing member of Damage's gang is foiled, when the dealer is mysteriously sent to a boot-camp style rehab center!
description.28: The Avengers take on Blastaar, ruler of the Negative Zone! Plus, the return of the Eternals!
description.29: It's Captain America against Crossbones, Baron Zemo, and Batroc's Brigade! Who will possess the Bloodstone? Plus: USAGENT VERSUS SCOURGE Part V: the true origin of Scourge!
description.31: Artifacts of unknown origin and power appear before Doctor Doom and Tony Stark at the same time. Doctor Doom is determined to possess both fabulous artifacts- even if it means tearing Stark International apart.
description.33: Eric Masterson must reclaim Mjolnir to become Thor once again--but the hammer lies in the clutches of DOOM! Can even the help of Hercules and She-Hulk overcome the mad monarch?
description.34: Several X-Men converge on Muir Island after strange, recent events draw them to the same place. Plus, Magneto makes a surprising announcement that affects the future of the X-team.
description.36: Brother Voodoo has been turned into a zombie! How can Moon Knight save him now?
description.37: The Punisher versus the Pentagon! Frank Castle is swept into a plot involving a nuclear submarine when he acts to a protect a whistle blower.
description.38: Morbius strikes! The Living Vampire is out for blood, and you'll never guess who’s on the menu -- Victor Strange, brother of the Sorcerer Supreme!
description.40: When Sniper hijacks an Apache helicopter, Punisher and Microchip gather a tank unit to chase him down!
description.43: Mysteries continue to unravel about Number Nine and her past. Shotgun ups the ante in his search for Skip's "genetically perfect woman." Can Daredevil save Number Nine...from herself?
description.45: The Reavers discover Wolverine missing and go on a hunt to recover him. Young mutant Jubilee may be in over her head as she must protect her new and battered acquaintance Wolverine, as well as escape the clutches of Donald Pierce and his ilk. Pierce unleashes his cyborg hounds, placing the two mutants in even more danger.
description.47: The return of the Original Human Torch! He debuted in 1939, and now he's back on the panels. This is one Golden Age throwback you don't wanna miss!
description.48: Iron Man returns!  What does this mean for the Avengers West Coast?!
description.49: What if the Vision had destroyed the Avengers? Plus, what if Wonder Man hadn't died?
description.50: What if the X-Men had lost Inferno? The Goblin Queen has brought hell to Earth, and the few remaining heroes, including Kitty Pryde and Doctor Strange, struggle to save what little of humanity is left.
description.52: Note: this issue does not collect reprinted material from UNCANNY X-MEN (1963) #133. ""Briggs' Revenge."" Storm meets a fellow mutant, but when she rebuffs his advances, things turn to battle! Wolverine and Colossus show up to assist, but it leads to a deadly choice for Ororo.
description.53: Note: this issue does not collect reprinted material from UNCANNY X-MEN (1963) #134. ""Fundamental Imbalance."" Nightcrawler befriends a young street performer, and they celebrate each other's differences.
description.54: Number Nine has escaped! The favorite creation of a mad geneticist is on the loose, and she's run straight into the path of Daredevil! Will 'Miss. Nine' be rehabilitated? Or will her natural instincts overwhelm? Special appearance by the Inhuman Royal Family!
description.55: In an alternate reality, Excalibur finds the lost cocoon of Rachel. Can our heroes retrieve their teammate before the Destroyer of Universes gets to it first?
description.56: Excalibur continues to dimension-hop, as Jamie Braddock is freed from Doc Croc's control. What havoc will Jamie unleash for Captain Britain and company?
description.57: The Hulk and Iron Man join forces to combat the Maggia.
description.58: Will Tony ever walk again? The doctors say NO but an experimental microchip says YES, or does it? What is really behind this convenient opportunity? Plus, after a court trial, it is revealed Kathy Dare has mental instability, and she's put behind bars!
description.61: Thor has merged with the mortal being Eric Masterson, and must learn to live two lives once again! But his first trial may be his most daunting, as he must contend with the greatest villain of all time--DOCTOR DOOM!
description.64: The Beast and Marvel Girl are reunited, but now they'll have to contend with a warlike faction of aliens!
description.65: While he's captured on an alien planet, Archangel has a flashback to old adventure!
description.68: Enter the dreams of the Human Torch! In Johnny's slumber, Crystal of the Inhumans rejoins the Fantastic Four, but not everyone is happy to see her back!
description.69: The Fantastic Four takes on their most tenacious foes yet - the Fantastic Four! Created by a rogue Watcher, will these deadly doppelgangers spell doom for Marvel's First Family?
description.70: Wolverine is being savagely tortured by the anti-mutant extremists known as The Reavers. In his semi-conscious state, Wolverine begins to hallucinate about the past and future for mutantkind.
description.77: Moon Knight has to deal with zombies when Brother Voodoo comes to town!
description.82: Conan is thrust into the middle of a haunting tale of cannibalism and deceit! He and his companions fight against the relentless forces of nature determined to consume them.
description.83: The Elixir of Darkness has blinded Conan!
description.84: What’s going on with the Smartship Friday, and how can Power Pack save their transport from going on the fritz? Time for a mission to Kymellia!
description.86: Guest-starring Captain America! As tensions boil over in Symkaria, Cap provides an assist to Spider-Man and Silver Sable. Will the trio be able to pull off a heist of ULTIMATUM's HQ? More truths revealed about the mysterious Solo.
description.87: In Symkaria, Captain America and Silver Sable confront Sabretooth, the true assassin of Symkaria's Prime Minister. Meanwhile, in the United States, Spidey and Solo track down the current ULTIMATUM big-wig. And on top of that, diplomatic relations between Symkaria and the U.S. have not only broken off, Symkaria's sending death squads after U.S. politicians!
description.88: Spidey on a mission of international espionage! Will Red Skull succeed in igniting war between America and Symkaria? And how do Skull's plans align with ULTIMATUM? Captain America and Spider-Man team up in a battle for American history!
description.89: Olympia, realm of the gods, sucked into the Negative Zone! Guest-starring the always quirky Great Lakes Avengers!
description.90: Cap, Batroc's Brigade, Baron Zemo, Diamondback, and the Living Mummy in a brutal free-for-all!
description.91: A shocking saga co-starring Power Pack and Cloak & Dagger!
description.92: The globe-spanning hunt for the legendary Bloodstone fragments finds Cap and Zemo on a South Sea island. But instead of the Bloodstone fragment, they might find death, for joining the hunt is a sinister fellow by the name of Crossbones!
description.94: Black Widow guest-stars to spin her own web of intrigue with Punisher!
description.97: Zaladane continues her path of destruction in the Savage Land. And this time, she's brought a few kidnapped X-Men with her! After drugging Havok and brainwashing Polaris' mind, Zaladane pits X-Man against X-Man with her expertise in mind-games.
description.98: Daredevil takes a stand against inhumane treatment of animals, when he helps a young ecologist take down her father's slaughter farm. But darker secrets lurk inside the barn, secrets that, if unleashed, would raise moral questions too grisly to answer!
description.99: Kitty is cast under a spell to be a "proper princess" in order to marry Prince William. Can Excalibur save their teammate from a frilly and obedient fate?

0.text: The Absorbing Man comes undone with cosmic might in this Acts of Vengeance crossover!

10.text: It’s a Moon Knight/Punisher team-up! Marvel’s most morally murky vigilantes must take down Ultimatum’s Flag-Smasher!

11.text: Ten years have passed since the Horde was eliminated and the world government collapsed. Now Strikeforce: Morituri discovers a new alien threat. What is the alien's plan for Mankind? The answer to that question will plunge Strikeforce: Morituri into its greatest adventure!

12.text: The ACTS OF VENGEANCE crossover saga begins here! One of the most powerful villains in the Marvel Universe has a long-standing grudge against the Avengers. This time he's come up with the ultimate plan to destroy them! Plus: Hawkeye and Iron Man embark on a desperate rescue mission to free guards trapped in The Vault!

13.text: Two ACTS OF VENGEANCE tales! It seems that nothing Hawkeye does can keep Crossfire down! Wait'll you see Crossfire's comeback! As Hawkeye discovers, it's sheer murder! Hawkeye takes on a suicide assignment - single-handedly stopping a mass escape of super-villains from the Vault!

14.text: An ACTS OF VENGEANCE CROSSOVER! Tandy and Tyrone are joined by the Avengers to take down the aptly named Assembly of Evil!

15.text: The Sunrise Society spins their expansive web throughout Japan, leading up to a political overhaul. But not if the Shadowmasters can put the kibosh in their plans!

20.text: A switch up with this issue’s creative team leads to She-Hulk’s world being turned upside down!

23.text: Nick Fury and co. uncover the truth about Baron Strucker and the Death's Head Commandos. The Death's Head Guards begin their coup by attacking NATO bases!

24.text: The Protector of the Universe teams-up with the Aquarian against Quantum!

25.text: Roughouse is abducted by a sinister cyborg, but Wolverine won't let a good sparring partner go that easily! Guest-starring Daredevil, the Man Without Fear!

26.text: Garm may look a bit look Fenris Wolf, but it’s infinitely more terrifying. And now the remaining New Mutants must stare Garm down at the misty gates of Hel!

27.text: Frank's plan to take down a drug-dealing member of Damage's gang is foiled, when the dealer is mysteriously sent to a boot-camp style rehab center!

32.text: Contains only Panther’s Quest Part 21: Losing Control. PANTHER’S QUEST PART 21: T’Challa sets out to confront Pretorius, but must first return Zanti Chikane safely home.

35.text: Jennifer Walters is put on a mission to investgate a murder! And the man who seems to have a lead on the case looks a lot like Santa Claus...

38.text: Morbius strikes! The Living Vampire is out for blood, and you'll never guess who’s on the menu -- Victor Strange, brother of the Sorcerer Supreme!

39.text: The Man, The Myth, The Magic! A special editorial on Doctor Stephen Strange, as told by Morgana Blessing.

40.text: When Sniper hijacks an Apache helicopter, Punisher and Microchip gather a tank unit to chase him down!

41.text: The history of the Death's Head Commandos revealed! Nick and Val attempt to rescue Kate Neville, but are instead struck down by dangerous mind-control!

42.text: The Gehenna Stone Affair concludes! Wolverine vs. Ba'al and vampires vs. everyone else!

44.text: Contains only Panther’s Quest Part 20: Great Cat in the City of Gold. PANTHER’S QUEST PART 20: T’Challa confronts Strike in Johannesburg to find out why Pretorius was after him.

46.text: The Human Torch guest-stars in this exciting issue that features Quasar and Torch battling the space time-skipping Angler!

51.text: Quasar takes to the stars to learn the true nature of his newfound powers!

52.text: Storm meets a new fellow mutant, but when she rebuffs his advances, it turns to battle!  Wolverine and Colossus show up to assist, but it leads to a deadly choice for Ororo.  Note: the issue does not include the reprint of Uncanny X-Men #133.

54.text: Number Nine has escaped! The favorite creation of a mad geneticist is on the loose, and she's run straight into the path of Daredevil! Will 'Miss. Nine' be rehabilitated? Or will her natural instincts overwhelm? Special appearance by the Inhuman Royal Family!

59.text: Contains only Panther’s Quest Part 19: Chances. PANTHER’S QUEST PART 19: Minister of Security Doeke Riebeeck and Sergeant van der Merwe catch up with T’Challa at Patrick Slade’s shop.

60.text: Magma recounts an adventure with the Prince of Power himself -- Hercules, son of Zeus!

65.text: While he's captured on an alien planet, Archangel has a flashback to an old adventure!

71.text: The Gehenna Stone fragments corrupt whoever bears them, so of course they end up in the most corrupt nation on Earth! Wolverine faces a war on all sides, while Ba'al heads straight to the top!

74.text: The Kree have created the ultimate anti-Silver Surfer weapon. And wait’ll you see who he is! Not only that, but the Kree launch an all-out attack on the Skrulls’ home planet!

75.text: The galaxy-spanning Kree/Skrull War reaches its peak!

76.text: She-Hulk and an incredible group featuring Razorback might not stand a chance against Xemnu!

78.text: Cloak takes on Ecstasy for possession of the Cloak of Darkness!

79.text: United as one strike force, Punisher and the Shadowmasters enter a lethal duel against the atomically powered Iris Green!

80.text: The Avenging Monica Rambeau goes supersonic in her own, high-flying adventure! Relive her past with Earth’s Mightiest and see her take down Powderkeg, Leviathan and Moonstone!

81.text: The Sunrise Society reemerges years after their last showdown with the Shadowmasters to dissemble their enemies’ base of operation. Only one true ninja will be left standing by issue’s end!

85.text: Celebrate the 30th anniversary of everyone's favorite canucklehead, Wolverine, with the newest addition to the Marvel Masterworks library!  Chris Claremont, Dave Cockrum and John Byrne took a little reprint series called X-MEN and turned it into the all-new, all-different titan that conquered comicdom.  Experience the thrills and excitement of these classic tales as the X-Men battle the mutant menace Proteus, the trickster Arcade (with a little help from the web-slinging wonder, Spider-Man!) and the White Queen!  Witness the emergence of Jean Grey as the Phoenix; Colossus' transformation into the Proletarian; and the first-ever appearances of Emma Frost, the Hellfire Club, disco-queen Dazzler and Kitty Pryde!  Featuring an introduction by the X-Father himself, Chris Claremont, this one's a must-have, True Believer!  Collecting X-MEN (VOL. 1) #122-131 and ANNUAL #3.

91.text: A shocking saga co-starring Power Pack and Cloak & Dagger!

93.text: Vampires on a Plane! Aerial combat brings Wolverine face-to-face with Ba'al, master of the Gehenna Stone - and, if he has his way, of the world!

94.text: Black Widow guest-stars to spin her own web of intrigue with Punisher!

95.text: Only trouble is brewing, as Nick Fury and company run up against the Death's Head Commandos. Who are the new members of Fury's strikeforce?

96.text: Contains only Panther’s Quest Part 18: So Many Nameless Enemies. PANTHER’S QUEST PART 18: T’Challa does battle with Elmer Gore and his mercenaries so Slade can finally tell him news of his mother’s whereabouts.
